The paper proposes a new approach to program synthesis using reinforcement learning and tree search. This falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the use of reinforcement learning, machine learning (cs.LG) for the supervised learning approach, programming languages (cs.PL) for the search-based techniques, software engineering (cs.SE) for the focus on program synthesis, and systems and control (cs.SY) for the use of Markov decision processes.
